# Governance Artifact Standards

## Patterns to Always Use
- Keep `DIRECTIVES.md` in sync with Taskmaster `tasks.json` after each session close.
- Reference `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for system truth; mark unknowns as `TBD — confirm before implementing`.
- Session start: follow `AGENTS.md` sequence exactly; session close: full checklist.

## Patterns to Never Use
- Marking more than one directive as In Progress in `DIRECTIVES.md`.
- Omitting Taskmaster task IDs from in-progress directive blocks when tasks exist.

## File Naming Convention
- Fixed names at repo root: `AGENTS.md`, `DIRECTIVES.md`, `SESSION_LOG.md`.

## Testing Requirement
- None automated; verify manually that Taskmaster state matches `DIRECTIVES.md` when closing a session.

## Context7 Library IDs (add "use context7" when using these)
- Not applicable unless editing scripts that call external CLIs.
